You must write a file to read all the files in a directory
The program is called from the command line

java ParseText books

Read in the list of common words provided

the program will open the directory books
and read in each file, strip out all punctuation
for each word, if the word is in the list of common words, count all occurrences of
words immediately  before or after

print each word combination that occurs more than 50 times.

--Shane:

To Run program:

cd into *src* folder and run command java parsefile.ParseFile Books